@startuml
' ============================================================
' Diagram   : Cloud Balancing - Cross-Cloud Routing & Failover
' Section   : 14.6 Cloud Balancing Architecture
' Type      : Component diagram
' Message   : An automated scaling listener routes requests to
'             redundant cloud service implementations across
'             multiple clouds while a failover system provides
'             cross-cloud resiliency.
' ============================================================

!include ../../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/interaction/sequence-diagram-style.iuml

title 14.6 Cloud Balancing\nCross-Cloud Routing and Failover

skinparam ComponentBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam ComponentBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam ActorBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam CloudBackgroundColor #F8FAFC
skinparam CloudBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF8DC
skinparam noteBorderColor #999999

actor "Cloud Service\nConsumer" as CSC

cloud "Routing Cloud" as RoutingCloud {
  component "Automated\nScaling Listener" as ASL
}

cloud "Cloud A" as CloudA {
  component "Cloud Service A\n(redundant impl)" as CA
}

cloud "Cloud B" as CloudB {
  component "Cloud Service A\n(redundant impl)" as CB
}

cloud "Cloud C" as CloudC {
  component "Cloud Service A\n(redundant impl)" as CC
}

component "Failover\nSystem" as FS

CSC --> ASL : requests
ASL --> CA : 1. route
ASL --> CB : 1. route
ASL --> CC : 1. route

FS .. CA
FS .. CB
FS .. CC
FS -[#B22222]-> ASL : 2. announce\nIT resource\nfailures

note right of ASL
  ASL must be aware of all redundant
  IT resource implementations within
  the cloud-balanced scope.
end note

note right of FS
  Provides cross-cloud failover so
  the architecture remains resilient
  to per-cloud platform failure.
end note

note bottom
  Resource replication may be incorporated when manual
  synchronization of cross-cloud implementations is not
  possible.
end note

@enduml

